However, the 2019 coronavirus disease (COVID-19) is a new disease, our awareness and knowledge are slowly improving based on ongoing research findings and clinical practice experiences; therefore, diagnosis and treatment strategies are also constantly updated.
In this letter, we have responded to a review of our guidelines and provided the latest diagnostic criteria for "suspicious cases" and "confirmed cases" according to the latest Covid-19 Diagnosis and Treatment Guidelines (seventh version) issued by the National Health Committee of the People's Republic of China.
