The diagnosis of a confirmed case should rest on a suspected case with any one pathogenic item or serological evidence as follows: (1) a positive real-time PCR test for SARS-CoV-2; (2) a sequence of the entire genome of the virus shows high homogeneity to a known positive novel of the coronavirus; (3) positive for IgM intestinal antibodies or IgG antibodies in the SARS-Co.
