Relevant reviews have been conducted by Whitby et al.
Commercial devices can measure and validate hand hygiene, if a demonstration of regulatory compliance is required.
The World Health Organization has "Five Moments" to wash hands:
After exposure to blood/body fluids
before the aesthetic, and
after treating the patient. The addition of antiseptic chemicals to the soap (soap "treated" or "antimycrobial") gives the agent a killer action.
